name: numericalguru
tag_list: numerical-reasoning, quantitative, data-interpretation, problem-solving, numeracy, numerical-tests, assessments
overview:
numericalguru provides numerical reasoning and data interpretation tests for those who need to practice for company assessments, b-school admissions, tests, and case interviews.

Passing numerical reasoning tests (often called data interpretation, numeracy tests) or case interviews is often crucial to pass first level assessments in consultancing companies, banks, accountancies, industry or b-schools. Graduates or professionals looking for jobs in these sectors need to be strong in quantitative ability and aptitude.

The company provides a couple of free practice quantitative aptitude and numerical ability tests and additional tests are available for paid members. Users can analyze test performance via graphical analysis tools and statistics and also use bookmarking as a way to keep track of questions that need extra attention.

GMAT quantitative ability practice tests are planned for the next stage of the rollout.
